PRESS DIGEST - Top Japan business news - July 27 . Following are some of the leading stories in the Japanese press on Friday , as reported by Kyodo news agency . NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN : - - Prosecutors to question Dai - Ichi Kangyo Bank Ltd ' s former chairman Kuniji Miyazaki and ex - chairman Tadashi Okuda in payoff scandal . - - Nine major electricals and software entities agree on compensation for digital recording property rights . ASAHI SHIMBUN : - - Most firms did not apply to use Labour Ministry ' s subsidies for child care and nursing care . MAINICHI SHIMBUN : - - Nomura Securities Co Ltd to file damages suit against its former president Sakamaki . - - Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto indicates retaining ruling party secretary - general Kato . 
